Project name: Cognitive implications in the lack of numerals of the Pirahã language



Data sources:

A)	Corpus of the Pirahã language:

 „This corpus provides a transcription and word-by-word translation of 1149 sentences of
 Pirahã that were collected during fieldwork by Steve Sheldon and Dan Everett. Our goal is
 to provide primary linguistic data from Pirahã in a human- and machine-readable format that
 includes annotation of the lexicon, morphology, and syntax of the language.“

Link to github repository: https://github.com/languageMIT/piraha





